This paper involves the use of neuromorphic hardware and deep learning techniques to analyze the efficiency of a neural network keyword spotter. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of power consumption and energy cost, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.ET (Embedded Systems).
